// Portaled label for the currently-active (or drag-targeted) notch.
// Rendered as a direct child of <body> so mix-blend-mode: difference blends
// against the page content below rather than being isolated by the rail's
// fixed-position stacking context. Color: #fff + difference yields automatic
// inverse-of-backdrop contrast — black text on light backgrounds, white text
// on dark backgrounds, without pixel sampling or per-section annotation.
//
// Positioning is split across two elements so framer-motion's `x` animation
// on the inner span does not overwrite the base CSS transform (see FB-156).
// Anchor owns `position: fixed` + the -100%/-50% placement; the inner span
// owns only the subtle slide-in `x` animation + opacity fade.
//
// `width: max-content` is mandatory — see FB-157. Without it, a block-level
// fixed div can be promoted to a GPU compositor layer before layout
// stabilises; the browser then resolves translate(-100%) against a stale
// width of 0, collapsing the entire X-offset to 0 and landing the label at
// left: r.left (right of the rail, clipping the viewport). The original
// `will-change: top, left` was the trigger for that premature promotion:
// top/left on position:fixed are not compositable properties, so the hint
// was incorrect and has been removed. The inner span carries its own
// `will-change: transform, opacity` which covers all animated properties.
//
// `mix-blend-mode` must sit on this anchor (whose parent is <body>, the root
// stacking context) — not on the inner span. The span lives inside the
// anchor's stacking context (created by `position: fixed` + `transform`), so
// putting blend mode on the span would isolate it to the anchor's empty
// interior and produce no inversion. Direct recurrence of AP-069. FB-156 §3.
.highlightLabelAnchor {
  position: fixed;
  width: max-content;
  transform: translate(
    calc(-100% - var(--portfolio-spacer-1x)),
    -50%
  );
  color: #fff;
  mix-blend-mode: difference;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-scrollspy);
  pointer-events: none;
}
```

